Please answer the below Data Structure Questions:

Q. why do we need data structure?
A.we need the data structure because it gives us an efficient way to store and organize data in a computer

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are the various operations that can be performed on different Data Structures?
A. Insertion, Deletion, Search, Sort, Traversal, Copy, Merge ...etc

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. List out the areas in which data structures are applied extensively?
A.numerical analysis, operating system, Artificial Intelligence, compiler design, database management, graphics,
statistical analysis ...etc

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is an Array?
A.Array is linear data structures, it is used to store multiple values in a single variable

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the Array and ArrayList?
A.An array has primitive data types as well as object data types. However.
 ArrayList has only object-type data entries

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is LinkedList?
A.A linked list is a linear data structure, it consists of nodes where each node contains a data field and a link
to the next node in the list.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How is an ArrayList different from Linked List?
A.ArrayList uses a dynamic array to store the elements
LinkedList uses a doubly linked list to store the elements

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between the HashTable and HashMap?
A.HashMap is non-synchronized whereas Hashtable is synchronized

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the major data structures used in the following areas : RDBMS, Network data model and Hierarchical data model?
A.Array is used majorly in RDBMS
Graph (HashMap) is used majorly in Network data model
Tree is used majorly in Hierarchical data model


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. How HashMap works in java?
A.HashMap stores the data in the pair of Key and Value, It uses an array and LinkedList data structure internally
for storing Key and Value

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException in java? When it occurs?
A.The ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException is a runtime exception in Java
it occurs when an array is accessed with an illegal index.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the different ways of copying an array into another array?
A.  - Create a new array of the same length and copy each element.
    - Use the clone method of the array. Clone methods create a new array of the same size.
    - Use System.arraycopy() method